$string['choosereadme'] = '<div class="clearfix"><div class="theme_screenshot"><h2>Starting from Scratch</h2><img src="scratch/pix/screenshot.png" /><h3>Theme Discussion Forum:</h3><p><a href="http://moodle.org/mod/forum/view.php?id=46" target="_blank">http://moodle.org/mod/forum/view.php?id=46</a></p><h3>Theme Documentation:</h3><p><a href="http://docs.moodle.org/en/Themes" target="_blank">http://docs.moodle.org/en/Themes</a></p><h3>Report a bug:</h3><p><a href="http://tracker.moodle.org" target="_blank">http://tracker.moodle.org</a></p></div><div class="theme_description"><h2>About</h2><p>Starting from Scratch is a fluid-width, three-column theme for Moodle 2.2 or higher. The custom menu contains a Home link which always appears to the very left, and a My courses and Login/Logout link, which appears after any administrator-added items.</p><p>Scratch has a settings page that lets you modify various background colours, custom footer, custom css, and the site logo.</p><h2>Tweaks</h2><p>This theme is built upon Base, a parent theme included in the Moodle core. If you want to modify Scratch, we recommend that you first duplicate it then rename it before making your changes. This means you\'ll still have the original files if you make a mistake. More information on modifying themes can be found in the <a href="http://docs.moodle.org/en/Theme">MoodleDocs</a>.</p><h2>Credits</h2><p>This theme was coded and is maintained by Miriam Laidlaw of HRDNZ. She can be contacted by email at miriam@hrdnz.com.</p></div></div>';

